unittitle_ssm: Fagen, Nelson, and Monahan family photographs
abstract_ssm: Collection primarily consists of photographic portraits and snapshots of members of Fagen, Nelson, and Monahan families of Brooklyn, dating from circa 1880s to 1930s. The photographs include cabinet cards, tintypes, and various types of black-and-white prints. Of note are photographs featuring a carousel, a man in a baseball uniform, and a portrait of the singer Chauncey Olcott. It also includes one photograph and advertisements for The Aden Mountain House in Parksville, New York.
